        void open()
        Opens the main URL of the Application Unter Test (configuration property: url.of.aut) in a new browser window and waits until the page is fully loaded. This method has to be called before most methods of the check(), perform() and verify() objects can be used.

      • addCustomHttpHeaderCommand

        void addCustomHttpHeaderCommand(String key,
                                String value)
        Tells the Selenium server to add the specified key and value as a custom outgoing request header. This only works if the browser is configured to use the built in Selenium proxy.
        Parameters:
        key - the header name
        value - the header value

      • switchToIFrame

        Parameters:

      • clickForDownload

        String clickForDownload(String elementType,
                        String elementName,
                        GUIElementLocator locator,
                        int taskCompletionTimeout)
        Clicks on an element and expects a download to start (e.g. a Download button or link). Downloads the file and returns it binary contents, in an encoded form.
        If no download starts within the given task completion timeout, a FunctionalFailure is thrown.
        Parameters:
        elementType - the type of the related GUI element to log
        elementName - the name of the related GUI element to log
        locator - to locate buttons, links or any other elements which react on mouse clicks.
        taskCompletionTimeout - the maximum number of milliseconds to wait for the completion of the task
        Returns:
        The binary contents of the file, as a Base64 encoded string; prefixed by the file name and a colon (e.g. myExcelFile.xls:AP8uMKg...).

      • waitForAjaxOperationEnd

        void waitForAjaxOperationEnd(String frameworkName,
                             int maxWaitTime)
        Waits for an AJAX operation to be finished. This is usually done with some JavaScript querying a variable of a known JavaScript framework (e.g. jQuery).
        The framework may or may not be supported by the web GUI implementation. If it is not supported, an AutomationException is thrown.
        If the maximum waiting time is reached without the Ajax operation being finished, a PerformanceException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        frameworkName - Name of the JavaScript framework to check, e.g. "jquery". Implementations should convert this parameter to lowercase before checking it, so case does not matter for the caller.
        maxWaitTime - Maximum time, in milliseconds, to wait for the AJAX operation to be finished.
